    <string name="login">Setup</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_header">Getting Started with EmberIot</string>

    <string name="login_instructions_app_1">To get started with EmberIot, make sure you\'ve created a
        n app in your Firebase Console and enabled the Authentication and Realtime Database modules.
        Once that\'s done, you can provide the necessary connection details. This can be done in
        two ways: you can either upload a <b>google-services.json</b> file or type the information
        manually on the next screen. Either way, you\'ll need to create an app in your Firebase Console.</string>

    <string name="login_instructions_app_2_header">Create Your Firebase App Configuration</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_app_3">Step 1: In the Firebase Console, navigate to Project Settings.</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_app_4">Step 2: Under the General tab, click the Add App button and select the Android platform.</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_app_5">Step 3: Set the package name to <b>com.emberiot.emberiot</b> and continue (you don\'t need to fill in the \"optional\" fields).</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_app_6">Step 4: Download the <b>google-services.json</b> file provided after continuing.</string>
    <string name="login_instructions_app_7">Step 5: Click the done button below, you will then need to upload the <b>google-services.json</b> file here.</string>

    <string name="login_login_instructions_header">Great!</string>
    <string name="login_login_instructions1">Your project is all set up! Now, you\'ll just need to
        create a user in your Firebase Console, and that\'ll be the one used to sign into the app.
        You can add as many users as you want and have them sign in on different devices too, if you\'d like.</string>
    <string name="login_login_instructions2">Step 1: Go to the Firebase Authentication page within the console.</string>
    <string name="login_login_instructions3">Step 2: Click the \"Add User\" button.</string>
    <string name="login_login_instructions4">Step 3: Enter the new user\'s info and add the user.</string>
    <string name="login_login_instructions5">Step 4: When that\'s done, click the \"Done\" button below.</string>

